SOUTH African billionaire Robert Gumede recently bought his 18-year-old son Robert Junior, a Porsche 911 GT3 for passing matric. In a video, they had fooled Robert junior into thinking his gift was a Porsche Boxter S, however the real gift was a 911 GT3. The 911 GT3 is a high performance version of the Porsche 911 sports car, which is mainly intended for racing. Robert Junior could not hold his excitement when he realised that they had bought his the Yellow 911 GT3. Robert Gumede is a South African businessman and philanthropist, who is the founder of IT firm Gijima Technologies and its holding company Gijima Group.  